=========
 SUPYLOG 
=========
| 

about
-----
| 

:author:  Bart Thate <bthate@gmail.com>
:contact: IRCNET/#dunkbots
:distribution: core
:license: Public Domain
 
| 

description
-----------
| 

log irc channels in supybot channellogger format

| 

  log irc channels in supybot channellogger format 

| 

commands
--------
| 

1) *supylog-cfg*

    :description: plugin configuration

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !supylog-cfg
        <output> options: channels=[] .. filenametimestamp="%d-%a-%Y"
        <output>  .. logtimestamp="%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S" .. nologmsg="-=
        <output>  THIS MESSAGE NOT LOGGED =-" .. nologprefix="[nolog]"
        <output>  .. version="GOZERBOT 0.9"


2) *supylog-cfgsave*

    :description: save plugin configuration

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !supylog-cfgsave
        <output> config saved


3) *supylog-off*

    :description: disable supylog on <channel> or the channel the commands is given in

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !supylog-off
        <output> supylog is not enabled in (gozerdata,#test)



    ::

        <user> !supylog-off #dunkbots
        <output> supylog is not enabled in (gozerdata,#test)


4) *supylog-on*

    :description: enable supylog on <channel> or the channel the commands is given in

    :permissions: OPER

    :examples:

    ::

        <user> !supylog-on
        <output> supylog enabled on (gozerdata,#test)



    ::

        <user> !supylog-on #dunkbots
        <output> supylog already enabled on (gozerdata,#test)


